According to the article, the United States is experiencing a surge in employment, with record numbers of Americans getting back to work. Currently, 17 states have reached or tied their lowest ever unemployment rates, while 20 states have jobless rates below 3%. Over the past year, the unemployment rate has decreased in every state, reaching historic lows in many cases. The article emphasizes that these figures represent real people finding good-paying jobs and being able to support themselves and their families. The author attributes this positive trend to their economic plan that focuses on growing the economy from the bottom up and the middle out. Although there is still work to be done to further improve the recovery and reduce costs for working families, the article highlights the significant progress made thus far.